# Answers (Optimized Solutions)

---

## Answer 1 — Top 3 Salaries per Department
WITH ranked AS (
SELECT *,
       DENSE_RANK() OVER(
           PARTITION BY dept
           ORDER BY salary DESC
       ) rnk
FROM Employee
)
SELECT emp_id, name, dept, salary
FROM ranked
WHERE rnk <= 3;
```
---

## Answer 2 — Running Revenue by Customer
SELECT customer_id,
       order_date,
       amount,
       SUM(amount) OVER(
           PARTITION BY customer_id
           ORDER BY order_date
       ) AS running_total
FROM Orders;
```
---

## Answer 3 — Latest Order Per Customer
WITH ranked AS (
SELECT *,
       ROW_NUMBER() OVER(
           PARTITION BY customer_id
           ORDER BY order_date DESC
       ) rn
FROM Orders
)
SELECT order_id, customer_id, order_date
FROM ranked
WHERE rn = 1;
```
---

## Answer 4 — Consecutive Login Streak
WITH cte AS (
SELECT user_id,
       login_date,
       LAG(login_date) OVER(
           PARTITION BY user_id
           ORDER BY login_date
       ) AS prev_login
FROM Logins
)
SELECT DISTINCT user_id
FROM cte
WHERE DATEDIFF(login_date, prev_login) = 1;
```

### Note

For 3+, more advanced gaps-and-islands later.

